What kind of brain is using Stellaris tactics for FT warfare?

The issue with FT (and PMT to an extent) is that it's Sci Fi. Ergo, it is fantasy in space. Even the most hard sci-fi of hard sci-fi nerds have to take so, so many creative liberties and assumptions just to get their humans off the ground and onto Mars, let alone space colonies around Jupiter with artificial gravity and self-sustaining oxygen and food supplies.

Therefore, using Stellaris is neither big brain nor small brain - but is simply how their particular brand of sci-fi runs.
